	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Speak to the merregon after peacefully resolving SHA_Orthon_TrespassLair&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Steps:&#xD;&#xA;1. Use roll amazing in debug&#xD;&#xA;2. goto -676; -754 in Shar Temple&#xD;&#xA;3. enter the room nearby, walk towards the piles of dead bodies&#xD;&#xA;4. cinematic starts. Pick 1 -&gt; 1 -&gt; 1 -&gt; 1 -&gt; 1 -&gt; 1 -&gt; 2&#xD;&#xA;5. wait for the troops to get into position&#xD;&#xA;6. use teleport S_SHA_Merregon_002 in debug" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="60" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="A merregon - a footsoldier from hell assigned to assist the Orthon ( a huge infernal bounty hunter). Outside of combat, the merregon is unspeaking and unreactive. Upon attempting to read its thoughts, you realise it's little more than an empty vessel, without personality or thought." />
